result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts.

10:08 AM Defendant Molly Ann Nessman appeared by phone.  Attorney Robert E Eaton appeared by phone for Molly Ann Nessman.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. Preliminary hearing requested, time limits waived. Bond already set and is to continue. Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived. Defendant moves to arraignment. Attorney Eaton asks that the timeframe for filing motions be left open at this time. Court grants the request.
